<subSubSection id="73FB72F0CE5012523D44FC47FD8AF8B6" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="description">
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5012533D44FC47FE4BFC74" blockId="12.[264,1075,876,937]" box="[264,421,911,937]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
(
<figureCitation id="A3DA3DFECE5012533D5DFC47FE70FC74" box="[273,414,911,937]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="13.[264,383,1403,1427]" captionTargetBox="[364,1228,531,1367]" captionTargetId="figure-177@13.[354,1233,529,1376]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Chrysotimus guangdongensis sp. nov. (male). 21. Wing; 22. first flagellomere, lateral view; 23. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048658" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048658/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Figs. 21–23</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5012533D44FC17FE0AFB94" blockId="12.[264,1323,991,1900]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis. Six strong dc, 1–2 irregularly paired acr. Palpus brown. Fore tarsomere 1 with row of 5–6 short v; hind tarsomere 1 with 8 erect short black ventral bristles on basal 1/5 and row of 6–7 pv.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5012533D74FB9FFBF1FBAC" blockId="12.[264,1323,991,1900]" box="[312,1055,1111,1137]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Description. 
<emphasis id="0995FD69CE5012533D83FB9FFDFBFBAC" bold="true" box="[463,533,1111,1137]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Male.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity id="FC198C9ECE5012533EF8FB9FFCFFFBAC" box="[692,785,1111,1137]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="1.9">1.9 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity id="FC198C9ECE5012533FE3FB9FFBF5FBAC" box="[943,1051,1111,1137]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="1.85">1.85 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5012533D74FBB7FD43FABC" blockId="12.[264,1323,991,1900]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Head metallic green with pale gray pollen; frons and face brilliant. Hairs and bristles on head yellow. Ocellar tubercle weak, with 2 very long oc and 2 very short posterior hairs. Lower postocular bristles (including ventral hairs) pale. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="A3DA3DFECE5012533814FB07FB40FB34" box="[1112,1198,1231,1257]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="13.[264,383,1403,1427]" captionTargetBox="[364,1228,531,1367]" captionTargetId="figure-177@13.[354,1233,529,1376]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Chrysotimus guangdongensis sp. nov. (male). 21. Wing; 22. first flagellomere, lateral view; 23. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048658" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048658/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) blackish; first flagellomere blackish, rather short, about 2/3 as long as wide; arista dorsal, with basal segment very short. Proboscis blackish, with brown hairs; palpus brown, with brownish hairs and 2 brownish apical bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5012533D74FAA7FAFDF8C4" blockId="12.[264,1323,991,1900]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Thorax metallic green with pale gray pollen, mesonotum and scutellum brilliant. Hairs and bristles on thorax yellow; 6 strong dc, 1–2 irregularly paired acr short and hair­like; scutellum with 2 pairs of bristles. Propleuron with 1 yellowish hair on lower portion. Legs including coxae yellow with all tarsomere 5 brown. Hairs and bristles on legs yellow; coxae with yellowish hairs and bristles; fore coxa with 3–4 anterior and apical bristles, mid coxa with 2–3 anterior and apical bristles, hind coxa with 1 brown outer bristle near middle. Mid femur with 1 av apically; hind femur with 1 av apically. Mid tibia with 2 ad and 2 pd, apically with 4 bristles; hind tibia with 2 ad, 2 pd, apically with 4 bristles. Fore tarsomere 1 with row of 5–6 short v; hind tarsomere 1 with 8 erect short black ventral bristles on basal 1/5 and row of 6–7 pv. Relative lengths of tibia and 5 tarsomeres of legs. LI 2.6: 1.5: 0.7: 0.6: 0.3: 0.5; LII 3.6: 2.2: 0.9: 0.7: 0.4: 0.5; LIII 4.0: 1.4: 1.0: 0.7: 0.5: 0.5.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5012533D74F8EFFC72F8B1" blockId="12.[264,1323,991,1900]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Wing hyaline (
<figureCitation id="A3DA3DFECE5012533DA8F8EFFDD5F89C" box="[484,571,1831,1857]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="13.[264,383,1403,1427]" captionTargetBox="[364,1228,531,1367]" captionTargetId="figure-177@13.[354,1233,529,1376]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Chrysotimus guangdongensis sp. nov. (male). 21. Wing; 22. first flagellomere, lateral view; 23. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048658" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048658/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
), veins brownish; R 
<subScript id="A765233ECE5012533F6AF8FCFCAAF898" attach="left" box="[806,836,1844,1861]" fontSize="7" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">4+5</subScript>
and M parallel apically, CuAx ratio 0.28. Squama yellow with pale yellow hairs. Halter brownish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5112523D74FED4FE3FFE83" blockId="13.[264,1323,284,470]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Abdomen metallic green with pale gray pollen, dorsum brilliant. Hairs and bristles on abdomen yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5112523D74FEA4FD73FE0B" blockId="13.[264,1323,284,470]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="A3DA3DFECE5112523DBAFEA4FDBFFE5B" box="[502,593,364,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="13.[264,383,1403,1427]" captionTargetBox="[364,1228,531,1367]" captionTargetId="figure-177@13.[354,1233,529,1376]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Chrysotimus guangdongensis sp. nov. (male). 21. Wing; 22. first flagellomere, lateral view; 23. genitalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048658" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048658/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Epandrium distinctly longer than wide, narrowing to apex, and with curved lateral process; surstylus thick, acute apically and curved upward; cercus round, with moderately long hairs.
</paragraph>
<caption id="6F9E71F3CE5112523D44FAB3FD49FA68" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048658" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5048658" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048658/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" startId="13.[264,383,1403,1427]" targetBox="[364,1228,531,1367]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph id="3B5E217BCE5112523D44FAB3FD49FA68" blockId="13.[264,1322,1403,1461]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="0995FD69CE5112523D44FAB3FE3EFA4E" bold="true" box="[264,464,1403,1427]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">FIGURES 21–23.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="FCE15AF8CE5112523D94FAB3FCFAFA4F" authority="Wang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2005" authorityName="Wang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2005" box="[472,788,1403,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guangdongensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0995FD69CE5112523D94FAB3FCFAFA4F" box="[472,788,1403,1426]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Chrysotimus guangdongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="12A64012CE5112523F50FAB3FC9FFA4F" box="[796,881,1403,1426]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(male). 21. Wing; 22. first flagellomere, lateral view; 23. genitalia, lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
